						<div class="postbody">It will basically cost a suitable FPGA training board, ones with plenty of on-board memory to hold a game now cost around $100. My ~$130 board (1.2M NEXYS2) can theoretically implement just about any *16-bit* arcade/console I know of and has 16 MiB of RAM and 16 MiB of Flash. Very powerful, but IMO very tiring to develop for because synthesizing/compiling is SOOO slow it makes debugging infuriating. I'd stick with a software virtual console (same goes for XGamestation people) until you're sure you know what you want and how to get there.</div>

