						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Celius wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">What would be really cool is a NES style system with 4BPP graphics even if there were no attributes (so you could have one 16 color palette for the entire background). Then perhaps the same would go for sprites. That might also eliminate complications with drawing graphics on screen. Though I don't know much about that.<br /><br />Also what would be cool is a sound chip with an extra square wave or so. Then maybe a triangle wave with adjustable volume. And then a sample channel with better quality than the DCM channel. But I might be taking all the fun away with these un-limitations.</div>
<br />
<br /> Umm, a PC-Engine? A 65x variant cpu at 7mhz, 4bpp tiles and sprites (each with their own 16 palettes), 6 channels that hold 32byte PCM samples each or individually switched into DDA mode for direct sample playing, all channels have 5bit log volume, and then 4bit channel pan volume per left/right, and master main/pan volume for the whole set.</div>

